{{Quote|Everywhere and every-when I went, it caused a [[Glossary#Nexus Event|nexus event]]. Sent up a smoke flare. Because I'm not supposed to exist.|Sylvie Laufeydottir to [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]|The Nexus Event}}
'''Sylvie Laufeydottir''', born '''Loki Laufeydottir''', is a Princess of [[Asgard]] who caused a [[Glossary#Nexus Event|Nexus event]] as a child and escaped the [[Time Variance Authority]]. Laufeydottir hid throughout the timelines while seeking revenge against the TVA and the [[Time-Keepers]]. On the cusp of her [[Release of the Multiverse|plan]]'s success, however, she was interrupted by another [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki Variant]], with whom she eventually formed an uneasy alliance. Having convinced Loki of the TVA's lies and manipulations, they worked together to fight them, discovering the Time-Keepers were fakes. With her only ally being Loki, Laufeydottir followed him into the [[Void (End of Time)|Void]], in the wake of [[Ravonna Renslayer]] sending him there, where they eventually [[Infiltration into the Citadel at the End of Time|found]] and [[Attack on the Citadel at the End of Time|confronted]] [[He Who Remains]], the creator of the TVA. Despite warnings from Loki about the consequences, Laufeydottir enacted her revenge and killed He Who Remains, causing the [[Multiverse]] to expand.

With her work complete, Laufeydottir retreated to [[Earth-3311987|one]] of the many new branches and made a quiet life for herself. Despite her wish to live a normal life, she would be forced to intervene once more in order to stop [[Dox]] and her [[Dox's Loyalists|loyalists]] from [[Attack on the Branching Timelines|pruning]] the new branches. When Laufeydottir discovered the existence of [[Victor Timely/Temporal Marvels|Victor Timely]], a variant of He Who Remains, she attempted to [[Chase of Victor Timely|kill]] him preemptively before ultimately deciding to spare him. Loki convinced Laufeydottir to return to the TVA, where she watched as they tried to salvage the [[Temporal Loom]]. In the end, Loki chose to [[Liberation of the Multiverse|destroy]] the Loom and weave the branches together by hand at the [[Citadel at the End of Time]]; Laufeydottir would recognize this act as Loki giving them a chance to fight for the free Multiverse she had been envisioning.

==Biography==
{{MD|Sylvie Laufeydottir (Earth-62171)}}
===Early Life===
====Learning of Adoption====
Loki Laufeydottir was born in one of the many realities that comprised what the [[Time Variance Authority]] called the [[Sacred Timeline]].{{Ref|WaldronInterview1}} As the Goddess of Mischief, she was raised on [[Asgard]] and was told by her parents early on that she was adopted.{{Ref|LK103}}

====[[Arrest of Loki Laufeydottir|Arrested by the TVA]]====
{{Quote|The universe wants to break free, so it manifests chaos. Like me being born the Goddess of Mischief. And as soon as that created a big enough detour from the Sacred Timeline, the [[TVA]] showed up, erased my reality, and took me prisoner. I was just a child.|Sylvie Laufeydottir|The Nexus Event}}
[[File:Little Sylvie playing 2.png|{{AltFloat}}|Loki playing in [[Asgard]]]]
One day, she was playing by herself with her toy action figures in the royal palace, when her playtime was disrupted by the appearance of a [[Timedoor]] behind her, along with Hunter [[Ravonna Renslayer]] and two [[Minutemen]] approaching her, stating she was under arrest. Renslayer grabbed the child by the arm and took her away from her toys to the Timedoor, kidnapping her, while a Minuteman put a [[Reset Charge]] on the ground to erase her parents and her reality.
[[File:Little Sylvie met the TVA.png|{{AltFloat}}|Loki being taken into the [[Time Variance Authority|TVA]]'s custody]]
Loki was taken through the Timedoor to the [[Time Variance Authority]]. While being led through by Renslayer, Loki watched as a man screamed and cried for help as he was taken into custody also.
[[File:Cute Sylvie scared.png|{{AltFloat}}|Loki goes under the procedures]]
She was then taken through the screening procedures and was given a TVA prisoner uniform. She stood before the TVA [[Minutemen|paperwork clerk]] and a TVA scanner clerk who motioned for her to pass under the screening to test if she was a robot or not. She hesitated but went through to the courtroom where Renslayer stood by her and presented her to the judge.
[[File:Little Sylvie uses the TemPad.png|{{AltFloat}}|Loki escapes using the [[TemPad]]]]
As Renslayer led Loki up to the front of the room, she bit Renslayer on the wrist breaking free and stomping on her foot before stealing her [[TemPad]]. She then produced a Timedoor using the TemPad and successfully escaped from the TVA.{{Ref|LK104}}

====Changing Her Name====
{{Quote|You changed your name. Brilliant."<br>"It's called an alias.|[[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] and Sylvie Laufeydottir|Lamentis}}
While on the run from the [[Time Variance Authority]], Loki adopted the name "Sylvie". As she grew older, she maintained a hatred for the TVA for kidnapping her and vowed to destroy them and their [[Sacred Timeline]]. She hid in apocalypses since the TVA could not detect a nexus event in an apocalyptic event.{{Ref|LK103}}

===Attacking the TVA===
====Attack in France====
{{Quote|Devil bearing [[Kablooie|gifts]].|[[Mobius M. Mobius]]|Glorious Purpose (Loki Season One)}}
Laufeydottir transported herself to [[Aix-en-Provence]], [[France]] in an alternate [[1549/TVA|1549]]. There she attacked a group of [[Minutemen]] from the [[Time Variance Authority]] by stabbing many of them. When she was spotted by a boy, she bribed him with [[Kablooie]], before grabbing the [[Reset Charge|reset charge]] and leaving, leading the boy to believe she was the Devil. She would later lure another group of Minutemen and slaughter them.{{Ref|LK101}}

====[[Ambush on the Minutemen]]====
[[File:Sylvie and fire 1x1.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir ambushes [[Minutemen]] in [[Salina]]]]
Laufeydottir later went to [[Salina]], [[Oklahoma]] in an alternate [[1858/A.I.M. Quantum Ore Shovel|1858]] and laid some oil around the area as a trap for the [[Minutemen]]. When they eventually came to analyze the [[Quantum Ore Shovel]] she used, Laufeydottir was spotted by the [[Time Variance Authority]], she then dropped a lantern she was holding and the fire in it followed the oil and started to burn the Minutemen. She spotted [[Hunter U-92]] escaping from the fire, but before he could reach the [[Reset Charge]], she dragged him back in and killed him before stealing it.{{Ref|LK101}}

====[[Kidnapping of Hunter C-20]]====
[[File:Loki Stills 128.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir kidnaps [[Hunter C-20]]]]
{{Quote|What are you doing?"<br>"Having some fun.|[[Minutemen|Minuteman]] and Sylvie Laufeydottir|The Variant}}
Laufeydottir then traveled to a Renaissance Faire in [[Oshkosh]], [[Wisconsin]] in an alternate [[1985/TVA|1985]], and set up another trap for a squadron of [[Minutemen]]. When they later showed up to the tent she was hiding in, Laufeydottir enchanted the commander of their unit, [[Hunter C-20]], and used her to fight and kill two of her subordinates. When [[Minuteman 200914867365 (Reset Charges)|Minuteman 200914867365]] asked C-20 why she was doing it, Laufeydottir responded to him through C-20 that she was having some fun, before releasing C-20 and stabbing the Minuteman herself. She then grabbed C-20's Tempad and opened a [[Timedoor]], before taking the other time charges and taking C-20 as her hostage.{{Ref|LK102}}
[[File:C-20 and Sylvie illusion 2.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir creates an illusion in [[Hunter C-20]]'s mind]]
Heading back to her hiding place in [[Haven Hills]], [[Alabama]] in [[2050s|2050]] in a [[Roxxcart Mall]], Laufeydottir set up her plan in case the TVA were to find her. Using her powers to trap C-20 in a memory, Laufeydottir discovered that C-20's mind had been cloudy and that the [[TVA]] were using previous Variants as hunters. Inside C-20's memory of a margarita bar, Laufeydottir posed as an old friend. C-20 asked Laufeydottir if she wanted anything to eat, and she played along by pretending to be concerned by the place's health record. 
[[File:Sylvie face.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir gets information from [[Hunter C-20]]]]
Once C-20 got a brain freeze, Laufeydottir told her that brain freezes are caused by cold things freezing the synapses of the brain to freeze memories in place. When C-20 did not believe her, Laufeydottir dared her to answer a question while having a brain freeze and C-20 agreed. Quickly drinking her margarita, C-20 told Laufeydottir to ask the question. Laufeydottir then asked C-20 how many people were guarding the [[Time-Keepers]], and when C-20 became suspicious, she changed the setting to night. She then assured C-20 that she could trust her, and C-20 told her that the way to the Time-Keepers was a gold elevator.{{Ref|LK103}}

====Encountering an Alternate Self====
[[File:Loki Chance 04.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir watches the cameras at [[Roxxcart Mall]]]]
{{Quote|So, you're the fool the [[TVA]] brought in to hunt me down."<br>"Me, I presume."<br>"Please. If anyone's anyone, you're me.|Sylvie Laufeydottir and [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]|The Variant}}
When the [[TVA]] finally did arrive in [[Haven Hills]], [[Alabama]] in [[2050s#2050|2050]], Laufeydottir enchanted one of the people at [[Roxxcart Mall]] and placed him on an aisle with a hurricane sale on azaleas where [[Hunter B-15]] and an alternate version of herself called [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] found her. Laufeydottir pretending to be the man said that he was there to check out the azaleas.
[[File:Female Loki EP2.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir revealing her true identity to [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]]]
However, when Loki and B-15 approached him, she decided to possess B-15, causing her previous host to collapse. Loki asked if the man was still alive, not knowing about B-15 being possessed, and Laufeydottir responded through her that they would usually wake up. Loki realizing that it was the Variant said that she was him, to which Laufeydottir said that it was more that he was her before smiling at him, to which he returned the pleasure. Laufeydottir left B-15's body and continued to talk to Loki through [[Roxxcart]] clerk [[Randy]].
[[File:Sylvie, the devil.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir bidding her farewell to [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]]]
Laufeydottir then stalled Loki by distracting him before possessing another man's body. Following a brief fight, she knocked Loki down and finished setting up the remaining reset charges. When Loki regained his strength and demanded to know what she was doing, she revealed herself to him. When the timer on the charges ran out, they were teleported using [[Timedoor]]s to [[Bombing of the Sacred Timeline|bomb]] different parts of the Sacred Timeline causing several nexus events. Once the bombing was finished, Laufeydottir escaped through a [[Timedoor]].{{Ref|LK102}}
[[File:Sylvie arrives on TVA.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir arrives in the [[Time Variance Authority Office|TVA]]]]
Laufeydottir was teleported to the [[Time Variance Authority Office]] and entered the hallway towards the office. Upon seeing [[Minuteman 75068293466]], she tried to enchant him, but her powers were unable to work within the TVA. She then engaged in hand-to-hand combat with three [[Minutemen]], using her physical skill and a Minuteman's [[Time Stick]] to wipe them out. She then approached an elevator with two more Minutemen guarding it, ignored their warnings to stop, and engaged in combat, using one Minuteman as a human shield before dispatching the others.
[[File:Sylvie back to Loki.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir getting challenged by [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] again]]
Before she could continue, Loki entered the room with two daggers and confronted her. When Loki tried to ask her questions, she asked why he had nothing better to do. When he asked if she was a Loki, she ignored him and told him to move. When he didn't, the two fought. Laufeydottir reacted with annoyance at Loki's idea to work together and his insult that she lacked vision and tried to leave. When Loki then tried to apprehend her, the fighting resumed, with her telling him to shut up before the two got locked in a stalemate.
[[File:Loki takes the TemPad.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir is confronted by [[Ravonna Renslayer]]]]
[[Ravonna Renslayer]] then entered with two Minutemen, and Laufeydottir overpowered Loki and threatened to kill him if Renslayer approached. Renslayer said she could, but before Laufeydottir could follow through, Loki stole her [[TemPad]] and teleported the two away from the TVA.{{Ref|LK103}}

===[[Escape from Lamentis-1]]===
====Fight for the TemPad====
[[File:Sylvie angry.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir angrily confronts [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]]]
Laufeydottir and [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] landed in a shed, and with the [[TemPad]] out in the open, Laufeydottir tried to recover it. Loki stopped her multiple times before recovering it himself, and Laufeydottir slammed him into an ash tray. She then took the TemPad off him before trying to leave, but the TemPad had run out of charge and she could go nowhere. Laufeydottir then tried to stab Loki, but he teleported behind her and pushed her into a nearby rack. When Loki took the TemPad back, she told him to give it to her as he didn't know how to recharge it. Loki said he did, as she wasn't the only tech savvy Loki, but she took offense to being called a Loki and told him to never call her that. As she lunged for the TemPad, Loki made it disappear.
[[File:Idiot!.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir learns she's on [[Lamentis-1]]]]
Laufeydottir then taunted Loki about being a magician, and Loki pulled out his daggers. Laufeydottir picked up her sword, but before another fight could break out, a purple meteor smashed through the roof and took them off guard. Laufeydottir asked where Loki sent them, and they left the shed to find they were on the moon [[Lamentis-1]] in the year [[2077/TVA|2077]], where an apocalypse was taking place in the form of a planet crashing into the surface. Laufeydottir called him an idiot for bringing them here, but Loki didn't know what she meant. Another meteor crashed down in front of them and the two ran for cover as Laufeydottir explained that this was the worst apocalypse saved in the TemPad and that no one survives. She almost got hit by a meteor, but Loki pushes her out of the way.
[[File:Sylvie under truck looking camera.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir takes cover with [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]]]
The two managed to take cover under a large truck, and Loki asked why she wasn't killing him, and she said that because he had hidden the TemPad, and if he dies it is lost. She then pointed to a mining shack to take shelter in and the two took off, but when Loki asked if they were a team, she said no. The two were bombarded by meteors on the way over, but the two safely made it inside.
[[File:Sylvie tries to control Loki.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir tries to control [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]]]
While Loki was catching his breath, Laufeydottir approached him and grabbed his face before trying to use her powers to trap him in a memory, similar to how she used her powers on [[Hunter C-20]]. It failed, due to Loki's strong mind. The two then drew their blades again, but Loki was tired of this and proposed a truce, which she scoffed at. She asked where the TemPad was hidden, but Loki jokingly said it was in his heart, so she threatened to cut it out. Loki told her to stop trying to kill him every 30 seconds, but Laufeydottir said that he was full of it as he needed her to figure out how to recharge it and that's why Loki saved her. Laufeydottir told him that her plan was years in the making, and that when she got the TemPad back, she'd go finish her plan, and then kill him.{{Ref|LK103}}

====Walking to an Abandoned Town====
[[File:Sylvie and Loki walking.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir and [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] exploring]]
She then left to find a power source to charge the [[TemPad]], and [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] accompanied her. The two trekked to a nearby town, and the two argued on the way, especially how Laufeydottir was a Variant but did not like to be called one, and also did not like to be called Loki. She then told him her name was Laufeydottir, and Loki told her that having an alias was not Loki-like. Laufeydottir then taunted Loki for working for the [[Time Variance Authority]], and said that he did not know what he wanted. He asked what he wanted, as he was confused why Laufeydottir would create a power vacuum so large in the TVA without planning to fill it herself, and that he never would do that. Laufeydottir said that she wasn't him.
[[File:Sylvie and Loki discusses out of house.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir asks [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] for the [[TemPad]]]]
When they arrived at an abandoned town, Laufeydottir noted that their fleeing was in vain as everyone died anyways. She then said they had about twelve hours before they would die along with them, and that it would get worse as the landscape changed and society collapsed. They then found a neon sign that was powered on, and Laufeydottir pretended to check the coupling before asking for the TemPad, but planned to leave and abandon Loki as soon as she took it. Loki saw through it and told her to try harder. Laufeydottir then told him to stop pretending to be tech savvy, as the TemPad required a large energy source to recharge, not just enough power to light up a sign.
[[File:Lmt2640 103 comp v031 20210609 r709.1068 r.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir and [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] speak to a woman]]
They then continued past the town and came upon a house with inhabitants. Laufeydottir grabbed her sword, but Loki stopped her, telling her that his diplomacy and guile would work better than her violence. She then kicked the door down, before being blown backwards by a woman with an air gun pointed at her door. She got up and Loki taunted her slightly before disgusing himself as the woman's late husband Patrice, but the woman wasn't fooled and he too got blown back. The woman taunted them calling them "devils" and then asked what they wanted with her, before Laufeydottir asked where everyone had went. She said they went to an evacuation vessel called the [[Ark (Lamentis-1)|Ark]], and Laufeydottir realized that the Ark could power the TemPad. Laufeydottir then learned that they could get there via train, but that there were no tickets left. She and Loki then left for the train at the edge of town, discussing how they would get on it.
[[File:Guards looking Sylvie and Loki.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir and [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] get on the train]]
The two found the train station, which had many people waiting outside to be let on. Loki then told her that they couldn't fight their way on, and Laufeydottir said her plan didn't involve fighting. Her plan was to enchant a guard to lead them through the crowd, and use him to kill anyone who stood in their way, probably killing all the guards and hijacking the train, and that it wasn't violent as whether there was a fight was up to the guards. Loki told her that they'd be doing this his way, before he transformed into a guard's outfit. While they passed by, the crowd yelled about how unfair it was that only the rich received tickets to salvation. The stepped up to the platform and when asked to see their tickets to Shuroo, Laufeydottir enchanted the guard to believe that headquarters had radioed a request for Laufeydottir to go to Shuroo that morning. The two then boarded the train.{{Ref|LK103}}

====Train to Shuroo====
[[File:Sylvie watching the lights.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir speaks with [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]]]
On the train, Laufeydottir and Loki sat down in a corridor and talked about their early life. Laufeydottir told Loki that she couldn't remember much about her mother, other than blips of a dream. However, Laufeydottir was interested when Loki discussed [[Frigga|his mother]]. Loki showed her a trick involving projecting fireworks that his mother had showed her. They then talked about their love lives, with Laufeydottir mentioning her long-distance relationship with a postman. Shortly after, Laufeydottir took a nap and when she woke up, she found Loki drunk and singing [[Asgardian]] chants with the rest of the passengers without his guards uniform. However, Laufeydottir noticed one passenger giving Loki a suspicious look and leaving to report on his behavior. Laufeydottir tried to get Loki to stop but they were confronted by multiple guards, which resulted in another fight and Loki getting thrown out of the train. 
[[File:Broken TemPad.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir sees the broken [[TemPad]]]]
Since he had the [[TemPad]], Laufeydottir followed him and jumped out also. After recovering from the fall, they found out that the TemPad was broken, much to Laufeydottir's anger. She was angered at Loki's carelessness and caused a small energy blast when she screamed to relieve the stress of impending death.{{Ref|LK103}}

====Making a Plan B====
[[File:Loki and Sylvie sit.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir is consoled by [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]]]
Laufeydottir sat down in defeat, while Loki followed suit and consoled her over his failure to protect the TemPad and asking her if the scream made her feel better. Loki then suggested that they still aim to escape, which would ensure their survival. Loki asks Laufeydottir if the planet that is about to crash into Lamentis-1 destroys the whole moon, which she confirms and adds that everyone on it is killed, including them. Loki asks about the Ark, to which Laufeydottir responds the Ark never leaves because it was destroyed. Then, with newfound confidence they start to make their way to [[Shuroo]] in hopes of making sure the Ark leaves, getting on, and using it to charge the TemPad to escape.{{Ref|LK103}}

====Struggle in Shuroo====
[[File:Sylvie and Loki running 3.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir and [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] in [[Shuroo]]]] 
However, upon entering Shuroo, Laufeydottir and Loki found it crowded and struggled to get to the front. Loki asked if all the people down below were going to be left to die, startled by that fact. Laufeydottir and Loki then went around the crowds through the backway before getting attacked by some more [[Lamentians|guards]].
[[File:Sylvie and Loki running 6.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir running for cover]]
Laufeydottir and Loki then had to take cover after asteroids began falling down over the city. As they were running, a building almost fell on them but Loki used his telekinetic powers to stop it and put it back up.
[[File:People see the Ark destroyed.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir witnesses the destruction of the ''[[Ark (Lamentis-1)|Ark]]'']]
When they reached some distance from the impact site, they observed a gigantic asteroid crashing into the ''[[Ark (Lamentis-1)|Ark]]''. Loki and Laufeydottir fearfully gazed at the Ark, as their only hope of survival was smashed to pieces. Upon seeing this, Laufeydottir walked away from Loki, having fully given up on their chances of survival, while Loki stood still in shock.{{Ref|LK103}}

===Fighting the TVA===
====Discovered and Recaptured====
[[File:Sylvie and Loki talking, and yeah, is not Black Widow.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir speaks with [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]]]
Having left [[Shuroo]], Laufeydottir and [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] sat down on the outskirts of the city and waited as the planet crashed into [[Lamentis-1]]. Laufeydottir told Loki about her past on [[Asgard]], being taken into the [[Time Variance Authority]] as a young child, and escaping them. She said she had been running from them her whole life, and wherever she went she caused a branch because she wasn't supposed to exist. She explained how she finally figured out how to hide out in apocalypses, and ending with she's grown up in them and now she'd die in one. Loki comforted Laufeydottir by marveling at her plan to solely take down the TVA. As two giant meteors hit the ground in front of them and creating a wave of earth and debris, Laufeydottir and Loki grabbed each other's hands. Just before they were enveloped in the wave, two [[Timedoor]]s appeared.{{Ref|LK104}}
[[File:Loki mid-season trailer 12.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir taken into [[Time Variance Authority]] custody again]]
Laufeydottir and Loki were then escorted back to the [[Time Variance Authority Office]], where they were arrested and separated by [[Mobius M. Mobius]] and [[Minutemen]]. Laufeydottir was then taken to an interrogation room where she was locked inside, with two Minutemen guarding the doors to make sure she did not escape. Becoming bored in the room, Laufeydottir rested her head on the table.{{Ref|LK104}}

====Hunter B-15's Request====
[[File:Tsc4020 104 comp v038.1069 r.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir is asked for help from [[Hunter B-15]]]]
Eventually, [[Hunter B-15]] walked inside and put aside her [[Time Stick]], surprising Laufeydottir. B-15 then asked for Laufeydottir's help before opening a [[Timedoor]] and asking her to accompany her. Laufeydottir followed and found herself back in [[2050s|2050]] [[Haven Hills]] outside the [[Roxxcart]] building. Laufeydottir was then asked to unlock B-15's memories, as B-15 had sensed something from the time when Laufeydottir had enchanted her. After B-15 remembered her past life, Laufeydottir smiled.{{Ref|LK104}}

====Killing the Time-Keepers====
[[File:Sylvie captured by Minutemen.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir is captured by [[Minutemen]]]]
Returning to the [[TVA]], Laufeydottir was recaptured by [[Minutemen]] and brought to where [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] was also in Minutemen custody. [[Ravonna Renslayer]] arrived and told the Minutemen that she would take care of them, leading them into an elevator. Inside, Laufeydottir asked Renslayer if she remembered her and Renslayer replied that she did. Laufeydottir then asked what her nexus event was, but Renslayer claimed that she could not remember.
[[File:Loki mid-season trailer 17.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir fighting the [[Minutemen]]]]
Laufeydottir and Loki were taken to the [[Time-Keepers]] chamber where they saw the Time-Keepers sitting on thrones before them. Laufeydottir tried to confront them, but Renslayer used a [[Time Twister]] on her. [[Hunter B-15]] then arrived and deactivated the collars around Laufeydottir and Loki's neck. She then gave Laufeydottir her [[Sylvie Laufeydottir's Sword|sword]] back, as Laufeydottir and Loki began fighting off the Minutemen, before getting confronted by Renslayer. Laufeydottir managed to knock Renslayer out before confronting the Time-Keepers with Loki.
[[File:Sylvie throws weapon.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir throws her weapon at one of the [[Time-Keepers]]]]
Ready to achieve her goal, Laufeydottir decapitated the head of one the Time-Keepers, only to find out that they were [[Time-Keepers|androids]]. This then left Laufeydottir and Loki confused and both asked the question of who founded the TVA. As Loki was about to say something to Laufeydottir, he was struck by a [[Time Stick]], and pruned by Renslayer.
[[File:Loki104 1218.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir threatens [[Ravonna Renslayer]]]]
Enraged that Renslayer erased Loki from the TVA, Laufeydottir promptly disarmed Renslayer and pointed her Time Stick at Renslayer. Renslayer then told Laufeydottir to prune her, but Laufeydottir refused and demanded that she tell her everything about the TVA.{{Ref|LK104}}

====Confronting Ravonna Renslayer====
[[File:Journey Into Mystery 01..jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir confronts [[Ravonna Renslayer]]]]
Laufeydottir took [[Ravonna Renslayer]] to the courtroom and threw her to the floor. She then kicked her forcibly demanding answers about the [[Time Variance Authority]] and demanded her [[TemPad]]. However, Renslayer told her she was in the dark about the TVA's origins just as much as she was. Renslayer then asked [[Miss Minutes]] to look into the files of the TVA's origins. As Miss Minutes scanned for the files, Laufeydottir was told by Renslayer that Loki was still alive and that she had sent him to a pocket dimension at the end of time. She then told Laufeydottir about a Void Timecraft, but Laufeydottir was doubtful.
[[File:Sylvie realises she was tricked.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir realizes she was tricked]]
Renslayer asked Laufeydottir to trust her and shook hands, but after Miss Minutes couldn't find the Timecraft, Laufeydottir realized that Renslayer was lying and jumped over the judge's seat to hide as [[Minutemen]] came inside to arrest her. Laufeydottir then stated that she couldn't have trusted Renslayer and asked her if she still wanted to find out the TVA's origins, before taking Renslayer's [[Time Stick]] and pruning herself.{{Ref|LK105}}

====Trapped in the Void====
[[File:Sylvie in Void.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir in the [[Void (End of Time)|Void]]]]
Laufeydottir woke up and found herself in the [[Void (End of Time)|Void]] in a broken down bus located in the ruins of [[Wrightsville Theatre|theatre]]. After smashing a window to get out, she was immediately found by [[Alioth]], a living cloud that consumed life and stripped all else bare. As she was running away from the being, she briefly enchanted it and viewed a foreign land and a [[Citadel at the End of Time|castle]], realizing that the being was guarding something of importance.
[[File:Sylvie in Car.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir speaks with [[Mobius M. Mobius]]]]
Shortly, a car drove up and the door opened for her to get in. When she hopped inside, she saw [[Mobius M. Mobius]] at the driver's seat. The two then discussed the [[TVA]], and Mobius apologized for Laufeydottir's kidnapping. After driving away from the being into [[Egypt]] and towards the [[Great Pyramid of Giza|pyramid]] and [[Great Sphinx of Giza|Sphinx]], Laufeydottir told Mobius to drive back towards Alioth as she had a plan.{{Ref|LK105}}

====Reunited with Loki====
[[File:Sylvie Mobius.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir and [[Mobius M. Mobius]] find [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]]]
Laufeydottir and [[Mobius M. Mobius]] eventually found [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]], and met [[Kid Loki]], [[Classic Loki]], and [[Alligator Loki]]. Laufeydottir then told Loki her plan to enchant [[Alioth]] in order to see what was beyond it and what it could be possibly guarding. At first Loki did not take her seriously, but agreed after Laufeydottir was confident with her plan.
[[File:Journey Into Mystery 08.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir talks with [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]]]
The group then waited for a branch timeline to appear and Laufeydottir sat down in the grass with Loki. As they were sitting, Loki conjured a blanket and shared it with Laufeydottir. Laufeydottir asked Loki if she could trust him after they had found out who was behind the [[TVA]] and he replied that he had changed for the better, so she could trust him.{{Ref|LK105}}

====Battle Against Alioth====
[[File:Loki mid-season trailer 7.png|{{AltFloat}}|Sylvie and [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] prepare for their plan]]
When Laufeydottir decided it was time to confront [[Alioth]], she handed [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] the [[TemPad]] she had gotten. However, he handed it to [[Mobius M. Mobius]] who opened a [[Timedoor]] and said goodbye to the two before leaving the [[Void (End of Time)|Void]]. [[Kid Loki]], [[Classic Loki]], and [[Alligator Loki]] left also, walking away, leaving Laufeydottir and Loki alone. Laufeydottir and Loki then watched as a warship was cast out into the Void and watched as Alioth appeared, completely devouring the sailors and leaving the ship in ruins.
[[File:Sylvie Enchants.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir enchants the [[Alioth]]]]
As Laufeydottir tried to maintain composure to enchant the Alioth, she needed a distraction so Loki offered and ran off to distract Alioth. However, Alioth ignored him and came for SLaufeydottir instead, but was distracted when Classic Loki returned and conjured up an illusion of [[Asgard]]. Laufeydottir continued to try and enchant Alioth, but grabbed Loki's hands and told him to join her in enchanting the being.
[[File:Sylvie Sees the Portal.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir and [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] see the [[Wormhole|portal]]]]
Together, they were able to enchant Alioth, but not without the sacrifice of Classic Loki, allowing the being to reveal what it had been guarding. Laufeydottir opened her eyes and told Loki to do the same, as they saw that a [[Wormhole|portal]] had opened up, revealing a [[Citadel at the End of Time|castle]] in the distance in another dimension. Laufeydottir and Loki exchanged glances and walked towards the portal.{{Ref|LK105}}

====Confronting He Who Remains====
[[File:Sylive Loki Castle.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir and [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] at the [[Citadel at the End of Time]]]]
{{Quote|You treated real people's lives like some kind of game."<br>"It's not personal, it's practical."<br>"It was personal to me.|Sylvie Laufeydottir and [[He Who Remains]]|For All Time. Always.}}
Laufeydottir and [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] walked up to the [[Citadel at the End of Time]] and waited outside, debating on if they should knock or kick the front door open. Laufeydottir told Loki to be quiet as she wanted to think about going in as she had been a victim of the [[Time Variance Authority|TVA]] forever. However, the doors to the castle opened up automatically, much to their surprise.
[[File:LokiSylvieMissMinutesTalkingForAllTimeAlways.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir and [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] speak to [[Miss Minutes]]]]
Laufeydottir and Loki walked in, with their weapons drawn, and turned around as the doors closed behind them. When they turned back around, they were startled by [[Miss Minutes]] who popped out of nowhere before them. Miss Minutes told them that [[He Who Remains]] wanted to make a deal with them and that he could make it work for both of them to be on the timeline together. Miss Minutes continued and told Loki that he could be victorious in the [[Battle of New York]], kill [[Thanos]], wield the [[Infinity Gauntlet]], and become king of [[Asgard]]. She told Laufeydottir that she could wake up and live in her happiest memories. However, Laufeydottir was skeptical and told Loki that it was all fiction, and she and Loki left the room.
[[File:Loki Sylvie see HE.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir and [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] meet [[He Who Remains]]]]
Walking into the next room, Laufeydottir and Loki found statues of what resembled the [[Time-Keepers]] with some on the floor. As they continued on, an elevator buzzer alerted them to it and they drew their weapons, standing in front of the elevator as it opened. The two watched as He Who Remains stepped out and greeted them, telling them to come on the elevator with him. Laufeydottir and Loki did cautiously, with their weapons still drawn.
[[File:Loki106 0346.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir tries to kill [[He Who Remains]]]]
In the elevator, Loki commented how He Who Remains was just a man, and Laufeydottir replied that that would make it easier to kill. She swung at He Who Remains with her sword only for him to use his [[TemPad]] and evade her swings rapidly. After He Who Remains transported himself out of the elevator, Laufeydottir looked angrily up at the ceiling, upset that she had been unable to attack him.
[[File:Loki106 0959.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir and [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] listen to [[He Who Remains]]]]
Inside He Who Remain's chamber, Laufeydottir and Loki were offered drinks and invited to sit down in chairs. The two eventually sat down and listened as He Who Remains explained his story about stopping the Multiversal War, how he harnessed [[Alioth]]'s power, and created the [[Time Variance Authority]] to protect the Sacred Timeline from the creation of his evil Variants.{{Ref|WaldronInterview1}} He then offered Laufeydottir and Loki a deal of what they could do if they cooperated with him. Laufeydottir was convinced that He Who Remains was lying, in which he suggested that she couldn't trust anyone, even Loki.
[[File:Loki stops Sylvie.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir tries to fight [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]]]
Laufeydottir stood up from the chair and tried to stab He Who Remains but Loki stopped her. This caused her to believe that Loki was power hungry and was not genuine; however, Loki tried to tell her that by killing He Who Remains, something more dangerous could come about. Not listening to reason, Laufeydottir engaged Loki in a duel and used her magic to blast Loki away so she could run at He Who Remains once more. After another attempt to kill him, Loki reappeared in front of her and stopped her.
[[File:Loki Sylvie kiss.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir kisses [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]]]
Laufeydottir listened as Loki told her that he had once been like her and knew where she was coming from, leading her to become emotional and drop her sword. She then kissed him, acknowledging their feelings for each other. After their embrace, she told Loki that she still was different and used He Who Remains' TemPad to open a [[Timedoor]]. She then used her powers to push Loki through it.
[[File:Sylvie confronts He.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir confronts [[He Who Remains]]]]
Now that Loki couldn't protect him, Laufeydottir confronted He Who Remains. Laufeydottir took her sword and with force, shoved the desk aside without touching it, leaving He Who Remains vulnerable, but amused, in his chair. She then walked up to him and asked if he was going to beg for his life. Finishing what she's started, she jabbed the sword in his chest, with him winking at her and telling her that he'll see her soon.
[[File:Sylive realizes.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir realizes what she's done to the [[Multiverse]]]]
Laufeydottir then realized that Loki had been right that He Who Remains was telling the truth. Realizing her actions and feeling upset that she was responsible for fracturing the [[Multiverse]], timelines now flowing indefinitely from the Sacred Timeline, she fell down on the floor and has an emotional breakdown. With no place to go, she remained alone in the empty Citadel.{{Ref|LK106}}

===Freedom===
====Trying Everything====
[[File:I Want Everything.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir realizes that she wants to stay]]
{{Quote|How do I do this?"<br>"What would you like?"<br>"Not squirrel, not possum, not rats. Something that's already dead, and nothing with a face... Please.|Sylvie Laufeydottir and [[Jack (McDonald's)|Jack]]|Ouroboros (episode)}}
No longer having to follow a pre-determined path, Laufeydottir traveled to a branched [[1980s/Earth-3311987#1982|1982]] in [[Broxton]], [[Oklahoma]]. She entered a [[McDonald's]] restaurant and asked for something not pertaining the likes of squirrels, possums or rats, and preferably something already dead and without a face. [[Jack (McDonald's)|Jack]], the cashier, offered available meals, to which Laufeydottir stated her intent to try everything.{{Ref|LK201}}

====Reunion with Loki====
[[File:She's Not Lovin' It.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir sees [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] at [[McDonald's]]]]
{{Quote|It's the future, it's going to happen."<br>"Is it? Really? Because that sounds a lot like the future's already been written. And we both know that it hasn't. Not anymore. I made sure of that.|[[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] and Sylvie Laufeydottir|Breaking Brad}}
Laufeydottir started working at the [[McDonald's]] and found herself enjoying it. While working, she refilled the straw dispenser and served [[Bill]] his food. She saw [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]], [[Mobius M. Mobius]], and a [[Time Variance Authority]] [[Hunter X-05|prisoner]] at the entrance to the McDonald's shocking her. Loki approached her register and greeted her. Laufeydottir returned the greeting and asked if he intended to order anything. Loki asked to talk, so she agreed to do so once on her break.
[[File:Loki and Sylvie (1982).png|{{AltFloat}}|[[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] tries to explain what he saw]]
They met in the parking lot, where Laufeydottir sat on her car trunk and ate. Loki acknowledged that she did not want to see him and assured her that he did not want to cause trouble. Laufeydottir asked why he was there, so Loki tried to explained that he was getting [[Time Slipping|pulled through time]]. Laufeydottir asked Loki to get to the point, so Loki explained that he saw her in the future at the [[Time Variance Authority Office]] and needed to know why. Laufeydottir sarcastically commented about Loki seeing the future and adamantly stated that she did not intend on returning to the TVA. She said that she did not care, and Loki insisted that future was guaranteed to happen, which upset Laufeydottir, since it sounded like TVA propaganda. Loki asked Laufeydottir to enchant him so she could see what he saw, but Laufeydottir said she wanted nothing to do with it. Loki told Laufeydottir that the situation was bigger than the TVA, which he saw as the only way to defend against a [[Multiversal War]].
[[File:Sylvie Brad Green Glow.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir enchants [[Hunter X-05|Brad Wolfe]]]]
Loki and Laufeydottir continued talking, but Laufeydottir had to return to her shift. Loki asked what Laufeydottir would if variants of [[He Who Remains]] appeared, but Laufeydottir simply said she would kill them. Mobius and the prisoner, [[Hunter X-05|Brad Wolfe]], joined them, ranting about how the entire timeline would die. Laufeydottir enchanted Wolfe and learned that [[Dox]] and her [[Dox's Loyalists|crew]] were planting [[Reset Charge]]s to destroy the branched timelines which Laufeydottir had created. She agreed to help them stop Dox's plan.{{Ref|LK202}}

====[[Attack on the Branching Timelines]]====
[[File:Sylvie Green Magic.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir destroys [[Dox]]'s equipment]]
{{Quote|The [[TVA]] is the problem. It's broken, it's rotten. I'm going home... if it's still there.|Sylvie Laufeydottir to [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]|Breaking Brad}}
Laufeydottir brought [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] and [[Mobius M. Mobius]] to where [[Dox]] and her [[Dox's Loyalists|loyalists]] were deploying the [[Reset Charge]]s, and the three made a plan. While Loki distracted the loyalists, Mobius and Laufeydottir went around destroying the [[TemPad]]s which were being used to set off the charges. Laufeydottir and Loki reunited and together created a powerful magic blast which defeated the remaining loyalists.
[[File:Sylvie Laufeydottir Season Two.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir expresses horror at the [[Time Variance Authority]]'s failure]]
Loki stayed with Laufeydottir while the loyalists were arrested by the [[Time Variance Authority]]. However, Mobius then told Loki they had to go. Loki turned to face Laufeydottir, who stayed in place as he left through a [[Timedoor]]. However, Laufeydottir ultimately decided to return to the [[Time Variance Authority Office]]. She saw as the entire TVA stood in shock at how many people had been killed in Dox's attack and got emotional at the destruction of the timelines. Loki approached Laufeydottir, who angrily asked if it was the best the TVA could do. Loki tried to explain that they could not do anything, but Laufeydottir did not accept the defense. Angry, she declared the TVA to be the problem and returned to her the timeline in which she had taken residency.{{Ref|LK202}}

====Return to 1982====
[[File:Sylvie talking to Jack.png|{{AltFloat}}|[[Jack (McDonald's)|Jack]] checks in on Laufeydottir]]
{{Quote|Is your mum on her way to pick you up?"<br>"Yeah. She'll be here. I'm good.|Sylvie Laufeydottir and [[Jack (McDonald's)|Jack]]|Breaking Brad}}
Laufeydottir returned to [[McDonald's]] and sat on the hood of her car in the parking lot. [[Jack (McDonald's)|Jack]] approached Laufeydottir and asked if she was okay, so Laufeydottir said she was. Jack then asked if Laufeydottir would be in work the following day, and Laufeydottir assured him that he would. Laufeydottir asked if Jack's mother was driving him home, and he confirmed that she was. Jack then walked away, and Laufeydottir looked at [[He Who Remains]]' [[TemPad]] as she activated it.{{Ref|LK202}}

===Tracking Victor Timely===
====[[Chase of Victor Timely]]====
[[File:Sylvie in 1893.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir threatens [[Victor Timely/Temporal Marvels|Victor Timely]]]]
{{Quote|When you showed up out of nowhere to ruin my life, you asked me what I would do if one of [[He Who Remains|his]] Variants turned up. And I told you then, I'd kill him.|Sylvie Laufeydottir to [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]|1893}}
Laufeydottir went to [[Before 20th Century/Temporal Marvels|1893]] on a branched timeline, where a variant of [[He Who Remains]] named [[Victor Timely/Temporal Marvels|Victor Timely]] was developing technology similar to that at the [[Time Variance Authority]]. She found Timely with [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] and pointed her sword at him. Loki put himself in front of the sword and tried to stop Laufeydottir, but she demanded he stay out of it and pushed both him and Timely into a Ferris wheel capsule. She told him to get out of her way and stabbed at Timely, who avoided the sword as Loki pushed her back.
[[File:Sylvie's Mission.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir reminds [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] of her promise]]
Laufeydottir reminded Loki of her assurance that she would kill any other variants who appeared, but Loki again got in her way and explained that the TVA would be destroyed without Timely. Laufeydottir said that they should let it burn and asked whether Loki cared about anything other than the TVA. Timely recognized the name of the TVA, so Laufeydottir lurched at them, but Loki explained that if the [[Temporal Loom]] were to fail, there would not be a life to which she could return. Laufeydottir pinned Timely to a wall using her magic and told Loki that working with Timely would not stop the TVA from being destroyed or fix it. She insisted that she would not like killing Timely, so Loki told her not to.
[[File:Sylvie Charging Up.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir attacks [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] and [[Victor Timely/Temporal Marvels|Victor Timely]]]]
Laufeydottir took the copy of the ''[[Time Variance Authority Official Handbook]]'' that Timely had and threw it at Loki, asked where Timely got it. She explained that without [[Ravonna Renslayer]]'s interference, Timely would not have been dangerous and scolded Loki for wanting to bring Timely into the TVA. Loki insisted that he had never met Timely and the TVA needed him, freeing Timely from Laufeydottir's magical grip. Laufeydottir charged at Timely, but Loki magically separated them. As the capsule stopped, Laufeydottir and Loki blasted at each other, sending Loki and Timely flying out one end and Laufeydottir crashing into the other. Laufeydottir watched as a crowd gathered and was chased off by [[Miss Minutes]] posing as the Ghost Clock of Midway, allowing Renslayer to escape with Timely. She found Loki on the ground and declared that it was his fault.{{Ref|LK203}}

====Confronting Victor Timely====
[[File:Sylvie Threatens Victor.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir prepares to kill [[Victor Timely/Temporal Marvels|Victor Timely]]]]
{{Quote|If you're gonna kill me, just do it."<br>"Oh, no. I've killed you a thousand times in my mind, each time more brutal than the last. It's crippling, that kind of obsession. I'm starting to realize that. It's power for you, isn't it? That's what you want. A seat at the [[Citadel at the End of Time|End of Time]]. Well, be careful what you wish for.|[[Ravonna Renslayer]] and Sylvie Laufeydottir|1893}}
Laufeydottir found [[Victor Timely/Temporal Marvels|Victor Timely]]'s [[Victor Timely's Laboratory|laboratory]] and walked in on [[Mobius M. Mobius]] and [[Ravonna Renslayer]] arguing about what to do with Timely. She blasted everyone over and approached Timely, pointing her sword at him. Timely insisted that he had not done anything, but Laufeydottir simply stated that he would. Timely claimed that Laufeydottir did not know who he would become, so Laufeydottir got emotional and told Loki and Mobius to leave with Timely. Laufeydottir hit Renslayer with the handle of her sword, so Renslayer said to simply kill her. However, Laufeydottir explained that despite having imagined killing Renslayer, she realized she had developed an unhealthy obsession. Laufeydottir noted that Renslayer wanted power and pushed her through a [[Timedoor]] to the [[Citadel at the End of Time]].{{Ref|LK203}}

===Destruction of the Temporal Loom===
====Return to the TVA====
[[File:Sylvie in the TVA.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir finds [[Victor Timely/Temporal Marvels|Victor Timely]] in the [[Time Variance Authority Office]]]]
Laufeydottir decided to return to the [[Time Variance Authority]] and found [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] and [[Mobius M. Mobius]] trying to convince [[Victor Timely/Temporal Marvels|Victor Timely]] to trust them. Timely greeted her and noted that everyone wanted him, demanding a say in his actions. A power surge occurred in the [[Time Variance Authority Office]], and Timely agreed to help once he realized that his [[Temporal Loom]] was responsible for it.
[[File:Somebody Killed He Who Remains.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir smiles at [[Ouroboros]]' comments about [[He Who Remains]]' [[Attack on the Citadel at the End of Time|death]]]]
Laufeydottir, Loki, and Mobius guided [[Victor Timely/Temporal Marvels|Victor Timely]] through the [[Time Variance Authority Office]], though he kept getting distracted by the technological innovations of [[He Who Remains]]. As Timely was introduced to [[Casey]] and [[Ouroboros]], Ouroboros and Timely realized that they had inspired each other's works and started complimenting each other and preparing to autograph each other's copy of the ''[[Time Variance Authority Official Handbook]]''. Laufeydottir interrupted them, asking them to focus on fixing the Temporal Loom. Ouroboros explained that someone would need to take the [[Throughput Multiplier]] to the Loom and launch it so that it could handle the branches, turning to Laufeydottir when he acknowledged that the branches were formed when she killed He Who Remains and ruined his life. Laufeydottir simply smiled at Ouroboros. Ouroboros said that the plan was doable, so Laufeydottir suggested they stop delaying. However, Casey noted that there was another problem. However, Timely correctly guessed the problem and offered a solution, so Laufeydottir left with Loki and Mobius to give them space to work.{{Ref|LK204}}

====Argument with Loki====
[[File:Sylvie Mad at Mobius.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir scolds [[Mobius M. Mobius]]]]
{{Quote|So [[Victor Timely/Temporal Marvels|Timely]] can save the [[TVA]]. Then, we hope that the TVA turns into something good. Then, we hope that Timely doesn't turn into [[He Who Remains]] or someone worse. That's a lot of hoping, [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]. I didn't have you down for an optimist.|Sylvie Laufeydottir|Heart of the TVA}}
[[Mobius M. Mobius]] suggested they have pie while they wait, causing Laufeydottir to become angry. Laufeydottir scolded Mobius for seemingly not understanding the stakes of their situation and leaving the problem solving to them after he and [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] begged for her help. Loki tried to calm Laufeydottir down, but she got angry about the dying timelines. She realized that Mobius had not looked to see what his life was like on the timeline, suggesting that Mobius did not understand the personal stakes before storming off.
[[File:Sylvie Stuck in TVA.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir listens to [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]]]
In Laufeydottir's wandering, she ended up in the automat, which was full of pies. She was about to leave, but Loki entered. Loki explained that Mobius was simply trying to figure out what to do like the rest of them. Loki mentioned that he had asked for help and she walked away, but Laufeydottir claimed not to have walked away, since she was in the [[Time Variance Authority Office]]. Loki suggested that she had only come since she could not kill [[Victor Timely/Temporal Marvels|Victor Timely]]. She explained that Timely appeared scared, whereas [[He Who Remains]] did not, although speculated that she simply did not see his fear. Loki shared that he had mocked [[Thor/New York Time Heist|Thor]] for the changes he had made while banished to [[Earth]], and Laufeydottir agreed that softness got people killed. However, Loki explained that by sparing Timely, she had ensure that the [[Time Variance Authority]] and the branching timelines would survive.
[[File:We Are Gods.png|{{AltFloat}}|[[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] reminds Laufeydottir that they are gods]]
Laufeydottir noted how much faith Loki had in Timely, [[Ouroboros]], and [[Casey]] and reminded Loki that [[Dox]] was part of the TVA as well and [[Attack on the Branching Timelines|killed]] several timelines. Loki claimed that the timelines which were still alive were due to the efforts of other members of the TVA, but Laufeydottir simply asked what would happen if Loki was wrong to believe the TVA could change, saying that it would be easier to destroy the organization and restart it. Loki agreed, but added that hope and trying to fix things was hard. Laufeydottir said that it was too much to hope for, but Loki insisted it was their best option. He went on to suggest sending Timely home after he helped could be a good thing since they could protect him. Laufeydottir implied it sounded like TVA propaganda, upsetting Loki. Laufeydottir noted that they appeared to be playing God regardless of what they did, but Loki simply stated that they were gods before walking away. Laufeydottir then followed Loki out of the automat.{{Ref|LK204}}

====Temporal Meltdown====
[[File:Sylvie Laufeydottir (Ouroboros).png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir finds [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]]]
{{Quote|There you are.|Sylvie Laufeydottir to [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]|Ouroboros (episode)}}
Laufeydottir and [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] found that [[Victor Timely/Temporal Marvels|Victor Timely]] had been taken and [[Miss Minutes]] returned. [[Hunter B-15]] arrived and said that [[Dox]] was killed, so Laufeydottir realized that Renslayer was responsible. [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] suspected that she was still in the [[Time Variance Authority Office]], so Loki and Laufeydottir rushed to look for them. The elevator door opened slowly, and Loki got shut out, so he took the stairs while Laufeydottir took the elevator. The elevator shut down on the way up, so Laufeydottir broke into the control panel and made it keep moving. However, the elevator again stopped moving.{{Ref|LK204}} Laufeydottir forced the door open and saw Loki. She expressed relief to see Loki, but he was then pruned{{Ref|LK201}} by the present version of himself.
[[File:Turn Off the Magic.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir and [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] ask [[Ouroboros]] to turn on the magic]]
Loki promised that things would made sense when the phone next to the elevator rang. Laufeydottir left the elevator and Loki answered the phone and realized that it was [[Ouroboros]] asking what was taking so long. Loki told him about Miss Minutes' sabotage, so Ouroboros suggested he reboot the system to shut her down. However, he was hesitant since it would mean losing the security protocols, including the one which dampens magic. Laufeydottir and Loki heard this and quickly told Ouroboros to shut it down, so he did.
[[File:Renslayer Pruned.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir prunes [[Ravonna Renslayer]]]]
Laufeydottir and Loki found [[Hunter X-05]], so Laufeydottir hid while Loki lured him over. Laufeydottir then enchanted him and found that Timely was in the War Room. As X-05, Laufeydottir entered the War Room and pulled Renslayer aside. She expressed surprise to see Renslayer again so soon while having her own body pull Timely out of the room with Loki. She used X-05's body to prune Renslayer before releasing him.
[[File:Sylvie's Last Moments.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir watches the [[Temporal Loom]]'s destruction]]
They rushed to the [[Temporal Loom]], and Timely opened the blast doors. Timely volunteered to be the one to bring the [[Throughput Multiplier]] to the blast doors, and he went to get ready. Laufeydottir asked how long he would have, but Ouroboros said it would not be long. As soon as the doors were opened, Timely was killed by the radiation, shocking everyone. Mobius asked where Timely was, so Laufeydottir simply stated he was gone and it was over. The Loom exploded, and Laufeydottir rushed in horror as the explosion moved toward the [[Time Variance Authority]].{{Ref|LK204}}

====Return to Her Reality====
[[File:Sylvie Didn't Forget.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir reveals that she did not forget her past]]
{{Quote|Of course I'm selfish. I want a life. I want to live. What's wrong with wanting something, [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]?|Sylvie Laufeydottir|Science/Fiction}}
Laufeydottir was returned to the timeline which she had lived in and continued working at [[McDonald's]]. At the end of a day of work, she brought food out to her car. However, while she was unlocking it, the food suddenly disappeared. [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] then appeared through a [[Timedoor]] and claimed that Laufeydottir did not know who he was. However, Laufeydottir explained that she did know who he was. Loki was surprised and explained that she was the only one of his friends who remembered. His body was nearly [[Time Slipping|pulled away]], but Loki stopped it. Laufeydottir, horrified by the display, offered to buy a drink for Loki.
[[File:Sylvie at Bar.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir tries to explain that the results of the destruction are positive]]
At the bar, Loki explained that the [[Temporal Loom]] exploding caused all of his friends to be forced into their lives on the timeline. However, Laufeydottir claimed that it was a good thing since they were back to the lives they were meant to have. Loki asked how many would have returned given the choice, but Laufeydottir reminded Loki that [[He Who Remains]] took their choice away. Loki suggested that people such as [[Mobius M. Mobius]], who enjoyed their lives in the [[Time Variance Authority]], should get to choose. Laufeydottir suggested that it would not be a fair choice to take people from their lives and show them the truth, but Loki simply restated that they did not get a choice and they could not get one without her.
[[File:Eric and Sylvie.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir gets [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] to confess what he wants]]
Laufeydottir did not care, prompting Loki to call her selfish. Laufeydottir agreed that she was selfish and that she wanted to live, asking what Loki wanted. Loki initially insisted that he wanted to stop [[He Who Remains]] and save the TVA, but Laufeydottir kept pushing him and got him to confess that he wanted his friends back. Loki explained that he did not want to be alone, so Laufeydottir said they were both selfish as Eric brought them drinks. Laufeydottir sympathized with the difficulties of Loki's situation, but claimed that his friends were where they belonged. Loki asked where he belonged, so Laufeydottir explained that they were writing their own stories. Laufeydottir told Loki to write his own story and left the bar.{{Ref|LK205}}

====Her Home Destroyed====
[[File:Sylvie Looks Up.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir watches as her universe is destroyed]]
{{Quote|There's nowhere left to go.|Sylvie Laufeydottir|Science/Fiction}}
Laufeydottir went to [[Rooster Records]] and greeted [[Lyle]], commenting on him staying late. Lyle realized she was having a difficult day and offered an album for her to listen to. She went to a record player in the back of the store and put the record in and enjoyed the listening to the song with headphones on. However, Lyle suddenly called out her name and started running to her, getting her attention. Laufeydottir saw the universe getting destroyed around Lyle and reached out to him, only for his hand to fall apart in hers. Laufeydottir sadly watched as the store was destroyed and used [[He Who Remains]]' [[TemPad]] to go to [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]].
[[File:Sylvie Spaghettification.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir is destroyed along with the universe]]
She arrived as Loki claimed that the friends he had gathered were fine without the [[Time Variance Authority]] and said that they were not. She explained that the branches were dying, but when [[Don/Don's Real Life|Don]] asked what it meant, Laufeydottir did not know and needed to do something. Loki suggested they go back and stop the [[Temporal Loom]] from melting down, telling [[A.D. Doug/A.D. Doug's Real Life|A.D. Doug]] that they had everyone they needed. Doug went to scan everyone's [[Temporal Aura]]s, but he and [[Frank Morris/Frank Morris' Real Life|Frank Morris]] disintegrated. Laufeydottir watched as Don and [[Verity Willis/Verity Willis' Real Life|Verity Willis]] disappeared along with the universe around them. Laufeydottir explained that there was nowhere left to go before she disintegrated.{{Ref|LK205}}

====Loki's Revelation====
[[File:Sylvie Back.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir brought back by [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]'s [[Time Slipping]]]]
[[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] [[Time Slipping|time slipped]] to [[Verity Willis/Verity Willis' Real Life|Verity Willis]]' death, bringing Laufeydottir back as she said that there was nowhere left to go. He then time slipped further back to her arrival at [[A.D. Doug/A.D. Doug's Real Life|A.D. Doug]]'s [[A.D. Doug's Workshop|workshop]]. [[Don/Don's Real Life|Don]] asked what it meant that the branches were dying, but Laufeydottir said she did not know. Loki suddenly realized that he controlled his [[Time Slipping]]. He then time slipped back to before the [[Temporal Loom]] was destroyed.{{Ref|LK205}}

====Looped====
[[File:Loki Takes Front.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir sits back and watches]]
{{Quote|[[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]... why are you being so weird?|Sylvie Laufeydottir|Glorious Purpose (Loki Season Two)}}
Now back in the [[Time Variance Authority Office]] due to [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]'s [[Time Slipping]], Laufeydottir did not retain any memories from after the explosion of the [[Temporal Loom]]. She watched as Loki quickly explained what to do to [[Victor Timely/Temporal Marvels|Victor Timely]] as if he was trying to prevent something. However, Timely died once again, leading to the loom's destruction. Laufeydottir and the others were looped many times as Loki tried to solve the problem, but it did not work.
[[File:Timely Dragged by Loki Sylvie.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir helps grab [[Victor Timely/Temporal Marvels|Victor Timely]]]]
Eventually, Loki time slipped earlier and called for Laufeydottir to help him. The two retrieved Timely from captivity and dragged him into the core room as Loki talked about wasting time. When nothing worked, Loki slipped to when Timely arrived at the [[Time Variance Authority]]. Laufeydottir trailed Loki as they made their way to [[Ouroboros]]' lab. Loki quickly told Timely and Ouroboros that they both wrote the [[Time Variance Authority Official Handbook]] before walking past Laufeydottir, brushing her. She flinched, asking Loki why he was being so weird.
[[File:Sylvie Suspicious.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir looks at [[Victor Timely/Temporal Marvels|Victor Timely]] confused]]
Loki neglected to answer and took Ouroboros' model of the loom. Laufeydottir helped him drag it to the middle of the room as he explained how they were going to expand the loom. Loki's quick explanations and knowledge made Laufeydottir suspicious, causing her to give him a threatening glare. Loki continued to explain asking if everyone was following, producing an annoyed yes by Laufeydottir. However, Ouroboros stated his doubts about getting the [[Throughput Multiplier]] running, leading Loki to conclude he had to do it himself, which would take centuries.{{Ref|LK206}}

====Realizing Her Mistake====
[[File:Sylvie in Focus.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir watches [[Victor Timely/Temporal Marvels|Victor Timely]]]]
{{Quote|It's almost as if as soon as the timelines started branching, this was doomed to happen.|Sylvie Laufeydottir|Glorious Purpose (Loki Season Two)}}
[[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] returned having spent centuries learning. He brought everyone to the core room where he tried to get started. Laufeydottir watched as Loki explained everything to a tea and typed in all of the codes needed. She then followed him to the windows where he used a microphone to talk to [[Victor Timely/Temporal Marvels|Victor Timely]] during the mission. Laufeydottir watched as Timely walked on the gangway and made it to the [[Maintenance Probe]]. There, he was able to dock it with the [[Temporal Loom]]. At this point, everyone cheered as Timely returned.
[[File:Sylvie's Fault.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir realizes it is her fault]]
This celebration was short lived, however, as Laufeydottir found herself inching away from the window as the loom started exploding. Despite Loki's confirmation that the calculations were correct, everyone saw their eventual demise unfolding. Timely then realized that they could not fix the loom as the [[Multiverse]] was infinite. So no matter how much they expand it, the loom would always fail. As everyone realized their fate, Laufeydottir spoke up, finally seeing the true danger of killing [[He Who Remains]]. If she had not killed him, this would not have happened. Loki then slipped away.{{Ref|LK206}}

====Replaying the Mistake====
[[File:Loki Fire Sylvie.png|{{AltFloat}}|[[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] pleads for Laufeydottir to stop]]
{{Quote|You've been seduced by a throne."<br>"The last thing I want is a throne. Sylvie, stop!"<br>"If you want me to stop, you'll have to kill me.|Sylvie Laufeydottir and [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]|Glorious Purpose (Loki Season Two)}}
[[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] [[Time Slipping|time slipped]] to before Laufeydottir killed [[He Who Remains]]. At the [[Citadel at the End of Time]], with her [[Sylvie Laufeydottir's Sword|sword]] pressed up against Loki's neck, he pleaded with her to stop. He then pushed her away, causing her to ask what was happening. Loki said that she had to believe him and that she could not kill He Who Remains.
[[File:Sylvie's Magic Blast.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir blasts [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]]]
Laufeydottir simply chalked it up to Loki wanting the throne, but he denied it. Laufeydottir replied that if he wanted her to stop, he would have to kill her. She then fought him and tried to get her sword to He Who Remains. However, she was stopped by loki, who grabbed her by the arm, causing He Who Remains to taunt Laufeydottir. She spun around and head butted Loki before blasting him away and stabbing He Who Remains. Loki then time slipped to remove this death.
[[File:Sylvie Sword Telekenesis.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir fights over control of her [[Sylvie Laufeydottir's Sword|sword]]]]
Now meeting He Who Remains for the first time in an elevator, Laufeydottir tried to make her first move, attempting to stab He Who Remains. However, Loki caught her arm, making the sword barely reach He Who Remains. Her enemy then laughed at her failure. Back at the top of the citadel, Laufeydottir threw her sword at He Who Remains, only for it to get caught telekenetically by Loki. Laufeydottir tried to push it further, but Loki brought it back towards then and slammed it to the ground before putting [[Laevateinn]] to Laufeydottir's throat. She repeated that he would have to kill her. Loki hesitated, then gave up his guard, allowing Laufeydottir to run and kill He Who Remains.
[[File:Frozen Sylvie.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir is frozen in place]]
This same routine happened countless more times as Laufeydottir refused to let up and Loki refused to kill her. Eventually, Loki pushed Laufeydottir away and asked He Who Remains why he would not do anything. He Who Remains responded by freezing Laufeydottir in place and then using his [[TemPad]] to remove her from visual. Laufeydottir was eventually freed and swung her sword, completing her motion when she was frozen. However, she realized something was wrong and looked around confused. This time, Loki froze her, learning a trick of his own. He Who Remains responded by making Laufeydottir disappear again.
[[File:Loki HWR Sylvie.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir reappears]]
He Who Remains eventually revealed a still frozen Laufeydottir once again and told Loki to either kill her or protect what they could as her killing He Who Remains set off the [[Temporal Loom]]. So he would have to kill her. Loki then slipped away.{{Ref|LK206}}

====Die Trying====
[[File:LokiStopsTime.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir is met by [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]]]
{{Quote|And who are you to say we can't die trying? Who are you to decide we can't die fighting? You're replacing one nightmare with another. I grew up in apocalypses, Loki. I've lived through enough of them to know that sometimes it's okay to destroy something.|Sylvie Laufeydottir to [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]|Glorious Purpose (Loki Season Two)}}
Laufeydottir was met by a [[Time Slipping]] [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] once again, but this time in [[A.D. Doug/A.D. Doug's Real Life|A.D. Doug]]'s world before being consumed by the [[Multiverse]]. She looked at Loki saying there was no where left to go. However, Loki surprised her by stopping time with a flick of his wrist. He told her that they were outside of time and he mastered his time slipping.
[[File:Sylvie and Loki.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir talks to [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]]]
Loki then broke the news that the [[Temporal Loom]] was designed to only protect the [[Sacred Timeline]] and the only way anything survived is if she never killed [[He Who Remains]]. This angered Laufeydottir, who was mad that they could never win and it was drawn up from the beginning. She then approached Loki and got close. She stared him in the eyes before breaking her gaze and chuckling. She told him that she was not giving him her blessing to kill her.
[[File:Sylvie Close Up (Glorious Purpose).png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir states her opposition]]
Loki looked back at her and simply told her that it was the Sacred Timeline or nothing and asked what he should do. Laufeydottir told him it was not enough to protect the timeline because everywhere there was death and destruction and he would be the god to take away everyone's free will for that. Loki asked what good free will was if everyone was dead. Laufeydottir told him that she lived in apocalypses and knew better than anyone that a little destruction can mean good and he could not say they could not die trying or die fighting. Loki then realized that she was right that destruction is good if you replace it with something better. He then time slipped away with an idea.{{Ref|LK206}}

====Given a Chance====
[[File:SylvieMobius.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir and [[Mobius M. Mobius]] are trapped by [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]]]
{{Quote|[[Loki/New York Time Heist|He]]'s giving us a chance.|Sylvie Laufeydottir|Glorious Purpose (Loki Season Two)}}
Laufeydottir was returned to the moment [[Victor Timely/Temporal Marvels|Victor Timely]] scanned his [[Temporal Aura]]. She then watched as [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] looked around solembly. He then calmly walked down the stairs without saying a word. Confused, Laufeydottir and [[Mobius M. Mobius]] followed him, only to be blocked by Loki who closed the door behind him. As Laufeydottir and Mobius pleaded for him to stop, Loki told them he knew what god he had to be for them and for everyone. He then opened up the door to the [[Temporal Radiation]].
[[File:Multiverse Rift.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir and [[Mobius M. Mobius]] watch [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]]]
Laufeydottir and Mobius ran up the stairs and to the window as they watched Loki walk down the gateway through pure will. As his clothes were ripped, it revealed a green cape and a [[Horned Helmet]]. They then watched as he used [[Magic]] to destroy the [[Temporal Loom]], causing dying branches to fall down. As the color faded to black around the [[Time Variance Authority Office]], the group watched as Loki took these branches as started giving them life through magic, opening up a rift to the [[Citadel at the End of Time]].
[[File:Giving Us a Chance.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir states [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]'s purpose]]
Loki looked back at the group. A sad Laufeydottir stared back as Loki faced the rift and started walking up an appearing stairwell to the citadel. As the rift closed behind him, Laufeydottir remarked at how he was giving them a chance, one that she never got. Loki then created the loom with himself in the center, causing him to be sitting at the [[Citadel at the End of Time]] forever.{{Ref|LK206}}

====A New Journey====
[[File:Mobius and Sylvie Watching Don.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir stands next to [[Mobius M. Mobius]]]]
{{Quote|It's weird that Loki's not here, isn't it?"<br>"Yeah."<br>"Well, see you around, I guess.|Sylvie Laufeydottir and [[Mobius M. Mobius]]|Glorious Purpose (Loki Season Two)}}
Laufeydottir soon left the [[Time Variance Authority Office]] to be on her own and ran into [[Mobius M. Mobius]] in [[2022]]. She approached Mobius from behind as he watched his [[Sacred Timeline]]-[[Don|self]] from afar. She remarked that the yard needed a little work, but Mobius admitted it did not and it was just perfect as it was the best house on the block.
[[File:Sylvie On Sacred Timeline.png|{{AltFloat}}|Laufeydottir is unsure of the future]]
Letting silence take the reigns, she spoke up, saying how it was weird that [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] was not there, to which Mobius agreed. She then said she would see him around. Mobius asked where she was going, but Laufeydottir had no idea. She asked the same and Mobius simply told her he was going to wait there and let time pass. She consoled him by grabbing his shoulder before leaving through a [[Timedoor]].{{Ref|LK206}}
{{Clear}}

==Powers and Abilities==
===Powers===
*'''Frost Giant Physiology''': Laufeydottir is a [[Frost Giant]] who has been enchanted to look like an [[Asgardian]] by her [[Asgardian Royal Family|family]]. Due to her heritage, Laufeydottir possesses all of the various superhuman attributes common among her people, including superhuman strength, durability, speed, agility, stamina, reflexes, healing, and was extremely long-lived.
**'''Superhuman Strength''': Like all Frost Giants, Laufeydottir possesses great superhuman strength. She was able to rapidly and easily yank and drag [[Hunter U-92]] away from a Reset Charge before killing him with her sword. Additionally she was able to effortlessly drag [[Hunter C-20]] through a [[Timedoor]] with one hand. During the [[Attack on the Time Variance Authority Office]], Laufeydottir was able to pull open heavy metal elevator doors to see [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]].
**'''Superhuman Durability''': Laufeydottir's skin is incredibly durable. She easily shrugged off a strike to the face from [[Ravonna Renslayer]]'s [[Time Stick]].
**'''Superhuman Speed''': Laufeydottir and Loki were able to outrun the meteors and destruction on [[Lamentis-1]], and she also outran [[Alioth]] in the Void.
**'''Superhuman Agility''': [[File:Sylvie kicks on face.png|thumb|250px|Laufeydottir fighting a [[Minuteman 75068293466|Minuteman]]]] Laufeydottir possessed impressive agility allowing her to battle [[Minuteman 75068293466]]. She was also able to spin her body on one hand while fighting [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] at the [[Citadel at the End of Time]]. She also used her powers to fight off [[Dox's Loyalists]].
**'''Superhuman Stamina''': Laufeydottir's endurance allows her to fight for long periods of time. She was able to run away from countless meteors on [[Lamentis-1]] and [[Alioth]] without taking a break.
**'''Superhuman Reflexes''': Laufeydottir can react and dodge objects traveling at high speeds. She was able to avoid the meteors on [[Lamentis-1]].
**'''Regenerative Healing Factor''': Laufeydottir could heal from wounds very quickly, including completely healing a scar on her eyebrow to the point where it was completely gone.
**'''Longevity''': Laufeydottir, like all other Frost Giants, are extremely long-lived beings. She was able to live past a thousand years while on the run.
{{Quote|You taught yourself that [[magic]]?"<br>"Yeah, I did.|[[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] and Sylvie Laufeydottir|The Variant}}
*'''[[Magic]]''': Like her [[Loki|original counterpart]], Laufeydottir is a powerful and skilled sorceress, capable of using [[magic]] to produce various effects. She can even cast weakened versions of her spells in the TVA, where no magic is supposed to function. She taught herself magic and was surprised to learn that Loki was taught by his [[Frigga|mother]].
**'''Enchantment''': [[File:Sylvie controlling C-20.png|thumb|250px|Laufeydottir enchanting [[Hunter C-20]]]] Laufeydottir can enchant victims by making physical contact and then grab hold of their mind, forcing them to fight on her behalf or obey her whims. She was able to make [[Alioth]] allow them to pass to the [[Citadel at the End of Time]]. Laufeydottir can use her enchantments to take complete control of other people's bodies, speaking and acting through them. She can also use her enchantment abilities through them, allowing her influence to transfer from one body to another by touch. This leaves the victim exhausted and drained, causing them to immediately pass out once she stops possessing them. She also enchanted [[Randy]] and [[Hudson (Guard)|Hudson]]. To figure out where [[Dox's Loyalists]] were, Laufeydottir enchanted [[Hunter X-05]] and later did so again to take over his body and prune [[Ravonna Renslayer]].
***'''Mental Manipulation''': Laufeydottir can easily compel a weak-willed person to engage in combat for her or believe whatever she tells them by merely touching them. However, someone with a strong will may be able to resist. Laufeydottir is able to combine her enchantment with another [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]'s, as they demonstrated it on [[Alioth]], forcing the being to open a portal for them. Upon touching someone, Laufeydottir can trap them in an illusion created from their own memories, forcing them to relive past events. This effect persists even after physical contact is broken and lasts until the memory playback ends, at which point the victim loses consciousness. While touching them, Laufeydottir can view their memories and even insert herself into the illusion, allowing her to interrogate them in an environment where they'll be more compliant and willing to reveal information. She was able to extract information about the [[Time Variance Authority]] from [[Hunter C-20]] and [[Hunter X-05]] by using this method.
***'''Power Bestowal''': When Laufeydottir enchants someone, she could bestow strength onto them. When she enchanted [[Hudson (Guard)|Hudson]], she was able to knock [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] across the room and incapacitate him while she made her escape.
**'''Energy Blast''': [[File:Sylvie rage 1.png|thumb|250px|Laufeydottir projecting a small energy blast]] Laufeydottir can project green energy bolts and blasts, allowing her to strike, push, or blow away her targets. The blasts are powerful enough to send an adult humanoid, as shown during her battle with her Variant over [[He Who Remains]]' fate, fire launching [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] several feet into a nearby wall with a single projectile. After distracting Loki with a kiss, she knocked him through a [[Timedoor]] with a close-ranged blast from her fingers. While holding hands with Loki, the two were able to create an even more powerful blast to stop [[Dox]] and her [[Dox's Loyalists|loyalists]]. Her blasts also destroyed a ferris wheel at the [[World's Columbian Exposition]].
**'''Telekinesis''': Laufeydottir is able to influence objects and move matter with mere gestures and focus. In a fit of fury and frustration, Laufeydottir inadvertently blasted air and dirt away from herself while screaming over the loss of the [[TemPad]]. After her final duel with her Variant, she further demonstrated her power by summoning her discarded sword off the ground and sending a large desk violently gliding across the room with a wave of her hand, a feat that impressed [[He Who Remains]].
**'''Illusion Manipulation''': Laufeydottir was able to transform between her civilian attire to a darker version of her outfit, as well as concealing both her [[Sylvie Laufeydottir's Sword|sword]] and [[He Who Remains]]' [[TemPad]] on her person as ordinary accessories, the latter appearing as a wristwatch.

===Abilities===
{{Quote|The Variant's been ambushing [[Time Variance Authority|our]] soldiers and hiding out in doomsdays to cover his tracks.|[[Mobius M. Mobius]] to [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]|The Variant}}
*'''Genius-Level Intellect''': Laufeydottir is very intelligent. She was able to figure out if she hid out in apocalyptic events, she would not cause any nexus events, a feat that was never achieved by the [[TVA]], let alone any of her other Variants, until a [[Loki/New York Time Heist|new Variant]] came along.
{{Quote|Your were just a child when the [[TVA]] took you, but you nearly took down the organization that claims to govern the order of time. You did it on your own. You ran rings around them. You're amazing!|[[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] to Sylvie Laufeydottir|The Nexus Event}}
*'''Master Tactician''': Laufeydottir is an excellent strategist and a very skilled planner, using her skills to stay out of the [[Time Variance Authority]]'s radar for years. She was able to plan out the [[Bombing of the Sacred Timeline]] and her [[Infiltration into the Time Variance Authority Office]] in order to take down the TVA and [[Time-Keepers]]. Once hearing about a Variant of [[He Who Remains]], [[Victor Timely/Temporal Marvels|Victor Timely]], Laufeydottir traveled to [[Before 20th Century/Temporal Marvels|1893]] to take care of him and ensure no He Who Remains emerged again to enslave the [[Multiverse]].
{{Quote|I just don't wanna be around a Variant who killed 400 of our co-workers.|[[Hunter X-05]]|Breaking Brad}}
*'''Master Combatant''': [[File:Sylvie kicks Loki.png|thumb|250px|Laufeydottir fighting against [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]]] Laufeydottir is a highly skilled and formidable hand-to-hand combatant, being able to fight [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] on equal ground, successfully defeated some of the most skilled warriors of the [[Time Variance Authority]], and almost effortlessly took down security guards on [[Lamentis-1]]. She was also skilled enough to temporarily hold back Loki while inhabiting the body of a [[human]] thrall. She battled skilled [[Minutemen]] many times including [[Dox's Loyalists]].
*'''Sword Mastery''': Laufeydottir is highly skilled at using a sword in combat, being able to stab and kill [[Minuteman 200914867365 (Reset Charges)|Minuteman 200914867365]] with ease, and even contend with [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] in melee combat several times. She also used it to fight against the guards of the train in [[Lamentis-1]] and the [[Minutemen]] protecting the [[Time-Keepers]] with ease.
*'''Expert Engineer''': Laufeydottir was able to take the stolen [[Reset Charge]]s and connect them to each other along with [[TemPad]]s in order to set up a switch to send each one to a timeline to [[Bombing of the Sacred Timeline|bomb]] it.
*'''Bilingualism''': Laufeydottir is fluent in her native Asgardian, as well as English.

==Equipment==
===Weapons===
*'''[[Time Stick]]''': Laufeydottir, while possessing [[Hunter C-20]]'s body, used the Time Stick against the [[Minutemen]] squad on the Renaissance Fair tent, in an alternate 1985. She later used it again to fight with the Minutemen in the [[Time Variance Authority Office]] during her [[Infiltration into the Time Variance Authority Office|attack]].
*'''Lance''': Laufeydottir used a jousting lance to attack the Minutemen in the tent while possessing Hunter C-20's body.
*'''[[Sylvie Laufeydottir's Sword]]''': Laufeydottir has a sword with Asgardian runes on it. She used it to stab and kill [[Minuteman 200914867365 (Reset Charges)|Minuteman 200914867365]], as well as to fight and threaten [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] several times. She also used it against the guards of the train in [[Lamentis-1]] and the [[Minutemen]] protecting the [[Time-Keepers]].

===Other Equipment===
*'''[[Horned Helmet]]''': As a Variant of [[Loki]], Laufeydottir also has a horned helmet, shaped like a smaller circlet and with a broken horn, that she can also use it as weapon in fight, shown when she shoved it at a guard during her fight on the train to Shuroo.
{{Quote|Just give it back to me. You don't know how to recharge it.|Sylvie Laufeydottir to [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]]|Lamentis}}
*'''[[TemPad]]''': Laufeydottir used a TemPad to teleport to different alternate timelines while collecting [[Reset Charge]]s and to escape the [[Time Variance Authority]]'s radar. However, her TemPad was stolen by [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] and later destroyed on [[Lamentis-1]].
**'''[[Timedoor]]s''': Laufeydottir uses these space-time portals of the [[Time Variance Authority]] to travel to apocalyptic events of the history to avoid being found by the TVA.
**'''Time Cells''': Time Cells are where the TVA's prisoners are put in a time loop for eternity, usually a reincarnation of a bad memory. Although Laufeydottir has the power to create one, she hasn't done so yet.
*'''[[Reset Charge]]s''': Laufeydottir collected many of these TVA devices in her ambushes to the [[Minutemen]]. She finally bombed the Sacred Timeline sending all of them to many points in the history, thus causing a complete chaos on the [[Time Variance Authority]].
*'''[[Quantum Ore Shovel]]''':Laufeydottir obtained this [[A.I.M.]] device during the earlier third millennium, and used it to ambush the [[Minutemen]] on an alternate 1858, in [[Salina]], [[Oklahoma]].
*'''Uniforms''': Laufeydottir used [[Hunter C-20]]'s uniform when she possessed her in the Renaissance Fair tent, and later used [[Hunter B-15]]'s uniform when she possessed her in the [[Roxxcart Mall]].
*'''Multifunctional Tool''': ''To be added''

===Vehicles===
*'''[[Lamentis-1 Train]]''': Laufeydottir and [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] boarded the train while trying to reach the ''[[Ark (Lamentis-1)|Ark]]'' to escape [[Lamentis-1]]. While on the train, she and Loki discussed their early life and Laufeydottir took a nap. After she woke up, Loki's cover was blown and he was thrown off the train. Since Loki had the [[TemPad]], Laufeydottir was forced to jump out of the vessel as well.

==Facilities==
{{Expand}}
*'''[[Royal Palace of Valaskjalf]]''': In her timeline Laufeydottir lived in [[Asgard]], residing in the Royal Palace. Laufeydottir played alone in the palace with her toys and action figurines until a [[Timedoor]] appeared and Hunter [[Ravonna Renslayer]] and two [[Minutemen]] grabbed her and arrested her.
*'''[[Time Variance Authority Office]]''': After she was arrested by the TVA, she went through the screening room, the signing room, the main room where Casey resides, and the judge room where she escaped from Renslayer. She went through the judge room once more where she forced Renslayer to tell her about the TVA, resulting in her pruning herself when she was cornered by Minutemen. She also was brought into a Time Theater to be interrogated.
*'''[[Roxxcart Mall]]''': Laufeydottir used the Roxxcart Mall as a place to lay low while hiding from the [[Time Variance Authority]]. She also used it to bring the captured [[Hunter C-20]] so she could find out how to get to the TVA.
*'''[[Citadel at the End of Time]]''': After she and Loki successfully enchanted Alioth, they entered the Citadel, and engaged in a battle over He Who Remains' fate, which ended when she sent Loki back to the TVA.
*'''[[McDonald's]]''': ''To be added''
*'''[[Rooster Records]]''': ''To be added''

